4 HR____ COMMENDING GRAYSON GAY FOR BEING NAMED A 2026
5 ALABAMA PUBLIC TELEVISION YOUNG HERO.
6
7 WHEREAS, highest commendations and congratulations
8 are proudly presented to Grayson Gay on being named a 2026
9 Alabama Public Television Young Hero; and
10 WHEREAS, Alabama Public Television selects Young
11 Heroes each year based on academic performance, service, and
12 resilience, highlighting students who have overcome
13 significant obstacles while continuing to contribute to
14 their schools and communities; each student receives a
15 scholarship and other prizes; and
16 WHEREAS, Grayson Gay is a junior at Cullman High
17 School who, after being diagnosed with stage three Hodgkin's
18 lymphoma in early 2025, stepped away from school activities
19 to undergo months of chemotherapy; and
20 WHEREAS, although cancer forced him to step away from
21 extracurricular activities and complete coursework
22 virtually, Grayson remained determined; throughout
23 treatment, he used social media to share encouragement and
24 faith-filled reflections, inspiring thousands in his
25 community; his message shifted from asking why he was facing
26 cancer to expressing gratitude for the strength it revealed
27 within him; his story resonated widely, drawing significant
28 community support and attention; and
Page 1

community support and attention; and
HR330 INTRODUCED
29 WHEREAS, now in remission, Grayson has returned to
30 campus and to the football field, regaining his strength and
31 preparing for the upcoming season; he adjusted his schedule
32 to include strength and conditioning to rebuild stamina and
33 position himself for a starting role; his oncology team has
34 been so inspired by his outlook that they have invited him
35 to mentor other children currently undergoing treatment in
36 the same cancer ward where he received care; and
37 WHEREAS, Grayson's servant heart extends throughout
38 his school and community; he is a member of Key Club and
39 Chick-fil-A Leader Academy; through these organizations, he
40 has helped organize service projects, including fundraising
41 initiatives and community meals for families in need; and
42 WHEREAS, Grayson maintains a 3.8 GPA while enrolled
43 in Advanced Placement and Dual Enrollment courses and is
44 preparing to take the ACT; despite the disruption of a
45 cancer diagnosis, he remains focused on his academic future
46 and aspires to pursue a career in pharmaceutical sales,
47 where he hopes to impact others in the health field; and
48 WHEREAS, Grayson Gay embodies resilience, faith, and
49 compassion; his courage in the face of illness, combined
50 with his commitment to serving others, makes him a powerful
51 example of strength and leadership; he is a deserving
52 recipient of recognition as a Young Hero; now therefore,
53 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
54 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That Grayson Gay is honored and
55 commended, and this resolution is presented to him in
56 highest tribute and with heartiest congratulations, as well
